modules.description: Prints a list of string lists as a formatted table to the terminal. Accepts rows of data where each row is a list of strings. Useful for displaying structured data such as query results or configuration summaries.

Prints a formatted table from a list of string lists, aligning columns and handling edge cases with exceptions. It operates on nested lists of strings, ensuring readable output for structured data. Used to display game board states in terminal-based applications.
